JOHANNESBURG –  A 40-year-old man was found dead on Tuesday on the M13 bridge in Sherwood, KwaZulu Natal. ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said when paramedics, along with other services, arrived at the scene at about 08:23 in the morning they found the man lying on the side of the road with fatal stab wounds to his chest. “Unfortunately, the man had already succumbed to his injuries,” said Meiring. He was declared dead on the scene. Local authorities are investigating the murder.
	
	  African News Agency